<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 93 / UK Company News: OFT looking at NatEx buy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Office of Fair Trading is currently examining the proposed takeover of
Citylink Coaches by National Express, Mr Neil Hamilton, minister of state at
the Department of Trade &amp; Industry, told parliament yesterday.
National Express, the coach service operator which was floated on the Stock
Exchange in December, announced on May 5 the acquisition of Citylink, the
main subsidiary of Saltire Holdings, for Pounds 5.11m in shares, loan notes
and cash.
