<DATE>930512
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 93 / UK Company News: GWR
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Great Western Resources, the US-based oil, gas and coal company which almost
collapsed last year following litigation with its largest customer, showed
significant improvement over the six months to end-March, when pre-tax
losses were reduced from Dollars 13.6m to Dollars 2.03m (Pounds 1.3m).
Total revenues of the USM-quoted group improved from Dollars 34.7m to
Dollars 59.1m, the bulk of which was derived from the coal operations, which
contributed Dollars 45.5m against Dollars 18.5m last time.
The dispute with the South Carolina Public Service Authority has now been
settled, and the net loss for the period, after a tax credit of Dollars
518,000 (Dollars 610,000), was Dollars 1.51m (Dollars 13m). Losses per share
came out at 2 cents (15 cents).
The company said it had signed a new credit agreement with Citibank, which
permitted a Dollars 34m capital programme for the year. Of this, Dollars
16.9m was spent in the period.
</TEXT>
