<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 93 / UK Company News: McLaughlin &amp; Harvey Pounds 6.8m in loss
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LOSSES AT McLaughlin &amp; Harvey, the County Antrim-based construction group,
widened from Pounds 5.4m to Pounds 6.8m pre-tax for the year to
end-December. Turnover fell Pounds 35m to Pounds 63.2m.
The deficit took account of a reduction in both interest charges to Pounds
1.09m (Pounds 1.71m) and exceptional provisions to Pounds 3.34m (Pounds
4.13m).
The group's principal objective for 1992 was to cut borrowings. At year end
these amounted to Pounds 6.7m (Pounds 11.2m). The reduction was partly
achieved at the expense of profitability, particularly in the housing
division where prices were reduced to secure sales and reduce exposure in
this sector.
Additionally, the sale of the Mallusk Park investment property made a
significant contribution.
</TEXT>
