<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 93 / UK Company News: Micro Focus and IBM relationship
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Micro Focus shares yesterday advanced to Pounds 24.28p before settling back
to close 58p higher on the day at Pounds 24.18p, on the news that the
company and IBM Programming Systems of California had expanded their
long-term relationship in mainframe operating software.
Micro Focus is licensing technology from IBM and will market it with a new
version of one of its existing products in the MVS (IBM's flagship operating
system) area, expected to be ready in September.
