<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 93 / UK Company News: Gold Crown in Pounds 16m buy-out
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Gold Crown Foods, a tea and coffee packer, has been acquired by a management
buy-out team backed by 3i and Henderson Venture Managers.
It is the second MBO at the company in six years. Total funding raised for
the buy-out was over Pounds 16m.
Originally part of Argyll Group, Gold Crown was bought by its management in
1987. This second MBO enables three of the four original buy-out team and
its backers to sell out.
