<DATE>930512
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 93 / Letter: Disastrously cocksure
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr I J BUFTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Another refreshing stream of opinionated political cynicism from Joe
Rogaly: 'A few (sic) local authorities changing political colour means
little now that the Tories have stripped so much power from the counties'
('Where comedy is king', May 7).
The government's disastrous electoral results that very day stem from many
factors. One was a cocksure assumption that ministers could trample over
local democracy with impunity.
I J Bufton,
