<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 93 / State labs expected to close
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BRONWEN MADDOX
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
STAFF AT Warren Springs Laboratories are expected to be told today that
closure of almost all of the government research centre is likely, according
to union officials, Bronwen Maddox writes.
Mr Jim Magee, national officer of the Institution of Professional Managers
and Specialists, said last night that Mr Douglas Cormack, the laboratories
chief executive, had told officials yesterday that the 'preferred option'
was the merger of about a third of the activities with other laboratories
and the closure of the rest.
Warren Springs, which has about 265 staff, is one of the DTI's five
laboratories, and is mainly engaged on environmental and energy research.
The DTI said last night 'no firm decision' had been made.
</TEXT>
