<TEXT>
THE BATTLE for the television screens of Britain's accountants has hotted up
with a solicitor's letter from one of the two competitors demanding that
remarks allegedly made about its financial status be withdrawn.
Accountancy Television, part of the BBC Select late night TV broadcasts, has
sent a request to Television Education Network (TEN) that it dissociate
itself from statements purportedly made by sales staff. No response has been
received.
A potential customer has written to Accountancy Television about remarks
they claim were made to them by a TEN representative. Mr Chris Bunyon,
marketing officer for TEN, confirmed the letter had been received but denied
the allegations. 'It is not our policy to defame the opposition. We are not
aware it has been happening.'
