<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 93 / Venezuelan court to rule on Perez
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CARACAS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
VENEZUELA'S supreme court announced yesterday it will rule on May 20 on
whether to send President Carlos Andres Perez for trial on corruption
charges in a case that could force him from power, Reuter reports from
Caracas.
Mr Perez and two former ministers face charges of embezzlement and misuse of
funds in the purchase of Dollars 17m (Pounds 11m) at a preferential exchange
rate and sale of the dollars in the free market for about Dollars 10m in
profit.
The government has denied the charges but declined to specify how the funds
were spent. The 70-year-old president, who has survived two coup attempts,
riots and a host of political feuds since taking office in 1989, would have
to step aside if put on trial.
</TEXT>
