<HEADLINE>
FT  12 MAY 93 / UN nuclear call to North Korea
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The United Nations Security Council yesterday called on North Korea to open
military sites to nuclear inspectors and reconsider its withdrawal from the
Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty, Reuter reports. The vote was 13-0 with
China and Pakistan abstaining.
While the resolution is fairly mild, it sets the stage for possible future
action, such as economic sanctions, though diplomats said there was no sign
the UN was contemplating such a move.
