<TEXT>
MR NORMAN LAMONT'S hold on the chancellorship was growing more precarious
last night after prime minister John Major refused to confirm that he would
present the first unified Budget in November, writes David Owen.
Mr Major - who minutes later said he was 'four-square' behind Mr John
