<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 93 / International Company News: TMM offers Dollars 200m paper in
US market
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SARA WEBB
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TMM, the Mexican shipping group, has launched a Dollars 200m bond issue in
the US domestic bond market, making it the first private-sector Latin
American name to tap the Yankee bond market.
The 10-year deal was increased to Dollars 200m from Dollars 150m in response
to strong investor demand.
The bonds carry a coupon of 9.25 per cent and were priced at 99.774 to yield
337 basis points over 10-year US Treasury bonds. Bear Stearns was lead
manager, with Goldman Sachs the co-lead for the deal. The bonds are callable
after five years.
TMM is Mexico's largest shipping company and operates ports and a trucking
company.
It is rated BA2 by Moody's and B+ by S&amp;P.
