<HEADLINE>
FT  11 MAY 93 / UK Company News: Exceptionals leave Pex Pounds 908,000 in
red
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pex, the knitted products manufacturer, reported pre-tax losses of Pounds
908,000 for the year to January 31 after exceptional reconstruction costs of
Pounds 790,000.
Towards the end of the year the company, formerly known as Palma Group,
liquidated subsidiaries, simplified the product range and wrote down
property values. The result was to improve reserves by Pounds 600,000. After
the year end, property was sold in Leicester for Pounds 1.4m which went
towards reducing debt.
The previous company reported a pre-tax loss of Pounds 278,000 for the 12
months to January 31 1992.
Turnover for the period under review was Pounds 14.5m (Pounds 17.2m).
Interest costs were Pounds 952,000 (Pounds 942,000) and losses per share
were 3.66p (1.47p).
