Less then 2 per cent of UK businesses are investing in foreign language
training for their staff, according to a survey carried out by Royal Mail
International.
A brief introduction to etiquette, letter writing and business practices in
Europe, Japan and the Middle East plus a French language cassette for the
traveller are provided in a Royal Mail guide for businesses dealing with
overseas contacts.
