These rates are published monthly by the Financial Times, normally around
the middle of each month.
A premium of 0.2 per cent is to be added to the credit rates when fixing at
bid. Interest rates may not be fixed for longer than 120 days.
SDR-based rates of interest are the same for all currencies but must be used
only for the OECD-defined poor countries.
For the period from Jan 15 through July 14, the SDR-based rate will be 7.55
per cent. It replaces the previous rate of 8.1 per cent. The SDR-based rate
will again be subject to change on July 15.
